article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 59, Md.-Eastern Shore 57
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Jimmy Hudson sank a 3-pointer at the buzzer to lift Bethune-Cookman to a 59-57 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore Monday night. UMES held an 11-point lead with 6:47 to play in the second half. BCC went on a 10-0 run for their comeback. Aaron Nelson came off the bench to score a game-high 22 points, and Bethune-Cookman defeated Maryland-Eastern Shore 59-57 Monday night. Aaron Nelson contributed 9 points and grabbed a team-high 7 rebounds for Bethune-Cookman (4-13, 2-6 MEAC). Corey Brown scored a team-high 17 points for UMES (3-16, 0-7).
